messages.text: Hey, next time you pick Beth up from school, can you PLEASE tell me first
I was worried sick when I couldn’t find her.
You mean last week?
No, I mean this afternoon.
I thought it was my day to pick her up, I would have loved a heads up
What are you talking about?
I’m at the office
I’ve been here all day
Mark you’re being really immature about this
It’s fine if you want some extra time with Beth, but we need to communicate
because otherwise I’m running all over the place trying to find my daughter and honestly I have better things to do.
This isn’t a joke
I didn’t pick her up from school
You’re not screwing with me right??
Because I’m gonna be really pissed if you’re screwing with me right now
I’m not screwing with you. I’m at work and I assumed you’d pick her up from school today.
WTF
Mark I’m freaking out
I came to the school at pick up time and I didn’t see her
I know sometimes it takes her a little extra time to get her stuff together
but when she didn’t come out I went in to find her teacher
She said Beth had already gone, I assumed because you took her
What the HELL is happening??
Cece I can’t focus on this right now
Can I call you in a little while?
Right, you’re always too busy for Beth
Not now Cece
Do you think maybe someone took her? Maybe her idiot teacher just let her leave with a stranger?
She didn’t have a playdate or anything
I need to call the police.
Mark, please call me.
a little bit later
Thanks for coming down to the precinct with me
Of course, how could I not?
We will find her. I promise.
When you brought her to school this morning, do you remember what she was wearing?
Um...haha I’ve never had a good memory for things like that
Well try! The police chief said we need a detailed description
Was she wearing pants or a dress? A t-shirt?
Oh yeah, I think she was wearing her Curious George t-shirt
Good, that’s a start
What did you talk about on the way to school?
Cece it was so early I hardly remember
I don’t think we really talked, it was early and she was sleepy
I keep telling you, you need to engage her in the morning to get her ready for the day
That’s what Dr. Fishman keeps saying
I will keep that in mind.
Actually, when I think of it, I remember her saying something about the zoo
The zoo?
Ok what did she say?
She keeps asking me to take her, and I promised I would soon
Nice to know you start the day with some empty promises
It wasn’t an empty promise
Look we can either be adults about this and work together to find our daughter
or you can continue to give me shit about every little thing.
All I remember is talking about the zoo.
I’m not going to be able to sleep tonight.
Can you meet me at the house?
You mean your house?
Yes.
I’ll be over soon.
two hours later
I just finished calling every parent in Beth’s class
Did you make it to the park?
Yeah, I’m here with a few of her friends’ parents
We’re all walking around with Officer McGuinness
Join us when you can.
Any clues?
No.
Do you think there’s any chance she went to the zoo?
Really?
It’s like twenty miles away, how do suppose she did that?
I don’t know, I’m just spitballing here
Does she even know where the zoo is?
My dad took her a couple of months ago
Oh! There’s no chance she’s with the grandparents, right?
No, my parents are out of town.
And you know my dad doesn’t drive, he wouldn’t have picked her up from school.
Oh yeah, I forgot he can’t drive anymore.
When he took her to the zoo they rode the bus the whole way
Beth thought it was all a big adventure
She thinks everything is a big adventure
My little pioneer :)
Wait!
Have you checked the bus station?
No, I didn’t even think of it
I’m gonna head over there, maybe she tried to get on the bus.
an hour later
Big news
Did you find her??
No not yet
But I came to the bus station, and the woman said that she saw a little girl here earlier
In a Curious George t-shirt
BETH!
Who was with her?
She was by herself
She tried to buy a bus ticket but didn’t have enough cash
I can’t believe this
You realize she did this because you wouldn’t take her to the zoo when she has asked countless times.
Please Cece, you can’t pin this on me
I work really long hours, it’s hard for me to get around to everything
You know that
But I love Beth more than anything. More than my job. More than life.
I know.
I do too.
The woman at the bus stop is giving me a lot of sass, but she said Beth walked into the diner down the road from the station
I’m going to run in and see if she’s there.
Well????
I think she was here
I mean, she was. She ordered a slice of cake and they served her for free
They just see a 7 year old girl by herself and instead of calling the police they serve her cake?
What kind of town do we live in?
So where is she?
They said she left when she was done.
You know, none of this would be happening if we had just gotten her a cell phone like I insisted
Dr. Fishman advised against it.
But you’re right.
I was wrong.
Wow, I never thought I’d live to hear you say those words
Gloat all you want, if we don’t find my daughter you’re dead meat.
She left here just half hour ago they said. She can’t be far away.
You should head home, just in case.
I just got in. No sign of her here. How about you?
She’s not at my place either.
Hold on...
Cece?
You there?
She’s safe! She's safe! I’m going to kill her but she’s safe!
Excellent! Where was she?
She walked home, and our neighbors invited her in until I got home
She was sitting in their living room
I’m over the moon
Thank god she’s safe
My little pioneer.
I have to get her to sleep. We can punish her tomorrow morning.
Good work, Watson.
Tell her that daddy loves her
And that we can go to the zoo this weekend.
Will do.
Hey Mark?
Yeah?
Thanks again. For everything.
Of course.
I’m sorry for being so rough. You know how heated I get
Oh I know...
You’re a good father. You really are.
You’re not too bad yourself :)
